# ============================================================
# WORLD CORE ARCHITECTURE
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: architecture
domain: world
scope: world.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines the canonical architectural role of world in CivilizationOS.

## design_intent
World is the bounded top-level environment
within which actors,
states,
nations,
organizations,
economies,
events,
and histories
exist and become meaningful.

World is not merely a map or visual backdrop.
It is the semantic containment boundary
for all lower-domain meaning.

## architectural_position
World sits above:
- life continuity
- nation jurisdiction
- time/map reference
- event occurrence
- policy/governance space
- organization/company activity space

## required_behavior
- world identity must remain explicit
- world boundary must remain explicit
- world membership and belonging rules must remain explicit
- cross-world distinction must remain explicit
- historical and current world states must remain distinguishable

## canonical_rules
- no lower domain may redefine world truth
- cross-world projection must not erase source-world identity
- current and historical world meaning must remain separate
- ambiguous world belonging fails closed

## state_model
The world domain distinguishes:
- declared world state
- active world state
- restricted world state
- historical world state
- archived world state

## actor_boundary
- world authority
- world operator
- reviewer
- integration adapter

## dependency
World architecture constrains
life,
nation,
map,
time,
event,
policy,
and all world-bounded operations.

## decision_matrix
- if world identity is unresolved, stop dependent execution
- if cross-world scope is unclear, fail closed
- if historical world reference is requested, preserve historical distinction
- if world is archived, preserve read trace and block invalid mutation

## review_checklist
- world identity is explicit
- world boundary is explicit
- dependent relation is explicit
- historical distinction is explicit
